Sentencas: Perovskite Sr1-xSexCoO3-delta (0.05 <= x <= 0.15) have been prepared by a sol-gel method and studied as cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Perovskite Sr1-xCexCoO3-δ (0.05 ≤ x ≤ 0.15) as Superior Cathodes for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: As SOFC cathodes, Sr1-xCexCoO3-delta materials have sufficiently high electronic conductivities and excellent chemical compatibility with SDC electrolyte.
Titulo: Perovskite Sr1-xCexCoO3-δ (0.05 ≤ x ≤ 0.15) as Superior Cathodes for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The peak power density of cells with Sr0.95Ce0.05CoO3-delta is 0.625 W cm(-2) at 700 degrees C.
Titulo: Perovskite Sr1-xCexCoO3-δ (0.05 ≤ x ≤ 0.15) as Superior Cathodes for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: By forming a composite cathode with an oxygen ion conductor SDC, the peak power density of the cell with Sr0.95Ce0.05CoO3-delta-30 wt %SDC composite cathode, reaches 1.01 W cm(-2) at 700 degrees C, better than that of Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-based cathode.
Titulo: Perovskite Sr1-xCexCoO3-δ (0.05 ≤ x ≤ 0.15) as Superior Cathodes for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: All these results demonstrates that Sr1-xCexCoO3-delta (0.05 <= x <= 0.15)-based materials are promising cathodes for an IT-SOFC.
Titulo: Perovskite Sr1-xCexCoO3-δ (0.05 ≤ x ≤ 0.15) as Superior Cathodes for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
